// liken carries three Go modules — one per domain that compiles: the
// init that boots the machine, the operator that manages it from inside
// the cluster, and the machine package they share (the Machine API as
// Go types). Separate modules keep each domain's go.mod an honest
// inventory of what that program links against; this workspace file
// tells the Go toolchain (and gopls) that they develop together, and
// each go.mod carries a replace directive pointing at ../machine so the
// modules also build standalone — the shared module lives in this repo,
// not on a module proxy.
go 1.26.4

use (
	./init
	./machine
	./operator
)
